Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives an estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older experts, who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database comprises 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and the required spare part is selected afterwards.
The user can include variables such as the price of work hours, surcharges or discounts, and then he can have the quote printed out and passed on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for reviewing such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the factory workshop does not involve an estimated working hours.
The cost of use for this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can pay without further use.
